<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4a.34.25.001" />
<fw type="curatorial">25</fw>
<note type="curatorial"></note>

<opener>
<address>
<addrLine>1138 Twenty-Second Avenue East</addrLine>
<addrLine>Eugene, Oregon 97403</addrLine>
</address>
<dateline>May 19, 1970
</dateline>
<salute>Dear John:</salute>
</opener>

<p>As you know we have made a Xerox copy of the manuscript of the Neihardt biography and sent it on to you to have as long as you like. It will also serve as the security copy in the event of the loss of the manuscript; but this event is I trust unlikely. The publisher has now acknowledged receipt of the manuscript.</p>

<p>I hope you like the book. It is the result of tremendous enterprise and patient research. In my judgement it is worthy of the highest praise; it is worthy of the great poet who is its subject.</p>

<closer>
<salute>Yours sincerely, now as ever,</salute>
<signed>Bower</signed>
<note type="authorial">Bower Aly</note>
<note type="authorial">Dr. John G. Neihardt
Lincoln, Nebraska</note>
</closer>

</div1>
